main event: A military pilot saw a large, brilliant light blue object at 35,000 feet over Blackstone, Virginia on February 17, 1955.
interesting points: The object was an extremely brilliant, large object.
The report was not further investigated due to lack of information in the original report.
An ATIC Form 164 was sent to the observer but no reply was received.
The sighting was concluded as 'Insufficient Data for Evaluation' and remained unresolved.
